Here’s a simplified JavaScript snippet showing how the game’s lighting could update as Sun Fragments are collected:

javascript
let collectedFragments = 0;
const totalFragments = 7;

function onFragmentCollected() {
  collectedFragments++;
  const lightProgress = collectedFragments / totalFragments;
  updateLightLevel(lightProgress); // Adjusts brightness from 0 (dark) to 1 (full light)

  if (collectedFragments === totalFragments) {
    triggerFinalSunrise(); // Endgame sequence
  }
}

function updateLightLevel(progress) {
  // Example: Modify ambient light and fog based on progress
  scene.fog.density = 0.01 * (1 - progress);
  ambientLight.intensity = 0.5 + 0.5 * progress;
}

This code increases brightness and reduces darkness effects proportionally as players collect fragments.
